ideas for Black that have been discovered lately in the main line introduced by
} 12. a4 {, it is just logical that the advance of the d-pawn has become
increasingly popular.}) 12... Nb8 13. Nf1 Nbd7 14. N3h2 Rc8 $5 $146 {An
interesting novelty. One important element of Black's plan is to break open
the centre with ...c6. However, this would weaken the d5-square and White can
try to take advantage of it by exchanging the f6 knight (with either Ng4 or
Bg5). The move played by Ivanchuk will be useful after a later ...c6 anyway 
(in some line given below, ...Rxc6 is possible), but refrains from defining
the position yet, waiting for White's reaction.} ({I have annotated several
lines where the topical line} 14... Nc5 15. Bc2 c6 16. b4 Ncd7 17. dxc6 Bxc6
18. Bg5 {was played.} Qc8 $5 {[%cal Yc8c3,Yc8h3]} (18... Qc7 {Carlsen,M (2765)
